==English==
===Etymology===
[[Christ]] is a respelling of Middle English '''Crist''' < Old English '''Crīst''' < Latin [[Christus]] < Greek [[χριστός]] ("[[anoint]]ed").

===Proper noun===
'''[[Jesus]] [[Christ]]'''

#A name for Jesus of [[Nazareth]], a [[Torah]]-observant [[Jewish]] man who [[Christian]]s believe to be the [[Messiah]] ([[Christ]]). [[Christ]] is not a name, but a title meaning "[[anoint]]ed (as the Messiah)".

